    <string name="instructions_markdown">
        ## What is PymeTask?\n
        PymeTask helps you manage tasks, contacts, notes, and files for your small business.\n\n

        ## Getting started\n
        - Sign in with Google or email.\n
        - Complete your profile in Settings.\n
        - Create your first task from the Dashboard.\n\n

        ## Tasks\n
        - Tap "New task".\n
        - Enter title, description, date and time.\n
        - Enable "Alarm" if you want a reminder.\n
        - Edit from list or detail.\n
        - Mark as completed when finished.\n\n

        ## Contacts\n
        - Create contacts or import from your phone book.\n
        - Add photo, phone and email.\n
        - From the detail screen you can call, send SMS, WhatsApp or email.\n\n

        ## Notes\n
        - Create quick notes, assign a color, and share via WhatsApp, email or SMS.\n
        - Edit/delete from the list or detail.\n\n

        ## Files\n
        - Create folders and upload files (images, videos, audio, PDF, Office).\n
        - Rename, share or delete from the context menu.\n
        - Files are uploaded to the cloud and metadata is stored in the database.\n\n

        ## Statistics\n
        - Filter by date range.\n
        - See categories and key indicators.\n\n

        ## Settings\n
        - Change language, theme (light/dark/system) and font size.\n
        - Reset preferences if needed.\n
        - Check version in "Info".\n\n

        ## Permissions\n
        - Contacts: to import from your phone book.\n
        - Storage/Media: to pick and upload files.\n
        - Phone/SMS: to call or send messages from a contact.\n\n

        ## Troubleshooting\n
        - If language doesn‚Äôt refresh, reopen the app (we also force it on ‚ÄúRecreate‚Äù).\n
        - If alarms don‚Äôt ring, check notification permissions and battery optimization.\n
        - Make sure you‚Äôre online when uploading/downloading files.\n\n

        ## Support\n
        - Email support@pymetask.app and include your app version (Settings &gt; Info).
    </string>

    <string-array name="faq_questions">
        <item>How do I change the app language?</item>
        <item>Can I change the font size?</item>
        <item>How do I enable task reminders?</item>
        <item>Why doesn‚Äôt the alarm ring?</item>
        <item>Can I import contacts from my phone book?</item>
        <item>How do I send WhatsApp, SMS or email from a contact?</item>
        <item>Where are my files and notes stored?</item>
        <item>Is there an upload size limit?</item>
        <item>How do I reset preferences (theme/language/font)?</item>
        <item>Can I edit or duplicate an existing task?</item>
        <item>How do I filter statistics by date or category?</item>
        <item>How can I contact support and what should I include?</item>
    </string-array>

    <string-array name="faq_answers">
        <item>Open Settings &gt; Language, pick one and the app will recreate to apply it.</item>
        <item>Yes. Settings &gt; Font size: Small, Medium or Large (applies app-wide).</item>
        <item>In the task form enable "Alarm", then choose date and time and save.</item>
        <item>Check notification permissions and exclude the app from battery optimization. Also confirm the date/time isn‚Äôt in the past.</item>
        <item>Yes. In Create/Edit contact tap "Import from phone book" and select a contact.</item>
        <item>From the contact detail use the action icons. You need a phone number for WhatsApp/SMS and an email address for email.</item>
        <item>Files are uploaded to the cloud and metadata is stored in the database. Notes and contacts sync with your account.</item>
        <item>There may be limits depending on your storage plan. Consider compressing large images/videos before uploading.</item>
        <item>In Settings tap "Reset preferences". Theme, language, font and internal associations are restored.</item>
        <item>Edit from list or detail. To duplicate, create a new one reusing fields (next improvement: duplicate button).</item>
        <item>Use the date range picker and category filters in Statistics. Refresh to see latest data.</item>
        <item>Open Settings &gt; Info to copy version and package. Email support@pymetask.app with a short description and, if possible, screenshots.</item>
    </string-array>




